SIMPLE: disclosure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disclosure
<hw>Dis*clo"sure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Disclose</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and cf. <er>Closure</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of disclosing, uncovering, or revealing;
bringing to light; exposure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He feels it [his secret] beating at his heart, rising to his
throat, and demanding <qex>disclosure</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>D.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is disclosed or revealed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Were the <qex>disclosures</qex> of 1695 forgotten?</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discloud</ent>⟦br⟧
